<section id="section-5">
<title>Exercises</title>

<para id="element-201a">
<exercise id="exercise-201a">
<problem id="idm3572368">
<para id="element-201">
In the arrangement shown, the acceleration of block “A” is 1 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
. Consider string and pulley to be mass-less and friction absent everywhere in the arrangement. Then,

</para>
<para id="element-202">
<figure id="fig-202">
<title> Pulley block arrangement </title>
<media id="idm4203808" alt=""><image src="../../media/npq6.gif" mime-type="image/gif"/></media>
<caption> Pulley block arrangement </caption>
</figure>

</para>
<para id="element-203">
(a)	The acceleration of block “B” is 1 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
.
</para>
<para id="element-204">
(b)	The acceleration of block “B” is 2 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
.
</para>
<para id="element-205">
(c)	The acceleration of block “B” is 0.5 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
.
</para>
<para id="element-206">
(d)	The acceleration of block “B” is 0.75 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
.

</para>
</problem>

<solution id="idp2645904">
<para id="element-207">
We are required to determine acceleration of block "B" to answer this question. By inspection, we observe that if block “A” moves “x” distance towards right, then the string length is distributed in two equal halves about hanging pulley. Clearly, if “A” moves by “x”, then “B” moves by x/2. As such, acceleration of “A” is twice that of “B”. As it is given that acceleration of “A” is 1 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>, the acceleration of “B” is 2 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>.

</para>
<para id="element-208">
Hence, option (b) is correct.
</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</para>


<para id="element-150a">
<exercise id="exercise-150a">
<problem id="idm5469360">
<para id="element-150">
Given : mass of block “A” = 0.5 kg and acceleration of pulley = 1 
<m:math>
  <m:mrow>
