</problem>

<solution id="idm6839552">
<para id="element-170">
Let “T” be the tension in the string. Here, spring force is equal to tension in the string. 

</para>
<para id="element-171">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>T</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mi>k</m:mi>
    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>200</m:mn>
    <m:mi>X</m:mi>
    <m:mn>0.1</m:mn>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>20</m:mn>
    <m:mspace width="1em"/>
    <m:mi>N</m:mi>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>

</para>
<para id="element-172">
Let acceleration of block “A” is “a”. Considering forces on block “A”, we have :

</para>
<para id="element-173">
<figure id="fig-173">
<title> Pulley block arrangement </title>
<media id="idp2442992" alt=""><image src="../../media/npq4.gif" mime-type="image/gif"/></media>
<caption> Pulley block arrangement </caption>
</figure>

</para>
<para id="element-174">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:mi>T</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mi>a</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
    <m:mi>X</m:mi>
    <m:mi>a</m:mi>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>

</para>
<para id="element-175">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:mi>a</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mfrac>
      <m:mi>T</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>10</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
    </m:mfrac>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mfrac>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>20</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
      <m:mrow>
        <m:mn>10</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
    </m:mfrac>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    <m:mspace width="1em"/>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
    <m:mo>/</m:mo>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mi>s</m:mi>
      <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>

</para>
<para id="element-176">
Considering forces on the mass-less pulley, we have :

</para>
<para id="element-177">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:mi>F</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    <m:mi>T</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
    <m:mi>X</m:mi>
    <m:mn>20</m:mn>
